perties. We fit two modified blackbodies to\nthe MIR and FIR SED, obtained by combining the $A_V$ map with data from Spitzer\nand Herschel. We derive effective temperatures (30 K and 227 K) and the ratio\nof opacities at 160 $\\mu$m to V band $\\kappa_{160} / \\kappa_V$ ($7.0 \\times\n10^{-4}$ and $2.9 \\times 10^{-9}$) for the two dust populations. Similar fits\nto individual pixels show spatial variations of $\\kappa_{160} / \\kappa_{V}$.\nThe analysis of our HST data, combined with these Spitzer and Herschel data,\nprovides the first panchromatic view of dust within a PDR.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 8 Nov 2019 17:41:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-15"}
