{x}_{\\mathrm{HI}} =\n0.55_{-0.13}^{+0.11}$ with scatter, compared to $\\overline{x}_{\\mathrm{HI}} =\n0.59_{-0.14}^{+0.12}$ without scatter, a very slight decrease and consistent\nwithin the uncertainties. Finally, we place our results in the context of other\nconstraints on the reionization timeline and discuss implications for future\nhigh-redshift galaxy studies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 8 Nov 2019 19:06:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 Apr 2020 21:41:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-13"}
